1 unit Sesame Ginger Chicken Gyoza
1 unit Vegetable Gyoza Dumplings

FRY:
1. Heat 1 TBSP cooking oil in a large pan over high heat. Add gyoza, flat sides down, and ⅓ cup water (be careful of splatter!); cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until water has evaporated and bottoms are crispy, 5-6 minutes.
2. Serve with gyoza sauce on the side for dipping.

BOIL:
1. Bring a medium pot of water to a boil. (Swap in chicken broth for water if you have some on hand!)
2. Add gyoza and cook until warmed through, 3 to 5 minutes.
3. Serve with gyoza sauce on the side for dipping.

MICROWAVE:
1. Place gyoza on a microwave-safe plate and cover with a damp paper towel.
2. Microwave until warmed through, 1 to 2 minutes.
3. Serve with gyoza sauce on the side for dipping.

***Chicken Dumplings are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.***